	<div class="comment-content__comment-body">
		<div class="comment-content__text" data-comment-text="2300681">
			<p>A bit US-centric??  Is the 'Account Updater' program available in Australia, and does this refer to cards that reach their expiry date and are replaced, or just ones that need to be replaced because you lost it or had it nicked?</p>
<p>I've never had any replacement credit card from Visa or M/Card that has a new number.  Only the expiry date has changed.  Also, I cannot ever remember Visa telling anyone my new expiry date.</p>
<p>Mrs Magani had 2 of hers replaced when some low-life nicked her handbag, but AFAIR, she had to do all the updating herself when the new cards arrived.</p>

			
